00:10:45.395 --> 00:10:48.356 align:middle line:84%
without ever sending men
and women into the desert,

00:10:48.356 --> 00:10:51.401 align:middle line:84%
risking their lives physically
to find those missiles.

00:10:51.401 --> 00:10:55.655 align:middle line:84%
It even located the plutonium
in North Korea in 1994

00:10:55.655 --> 00:10:58.157 align:middle line:84%
when there was a question
as to where North Korea was

00:10:58.157 --> 00:11:00.201 align:middle line:90%
in their nuclear program.

00:11:00.201 --> 00:11:02.453 align:middle line:84%
The success of the remote
viewing experiments

00:11:02.453 --> 00:11:04.122 align:middle line:90%
poses a key question.

00:11:04.122 --> 00:11:06.958 align:middle line:84%
And the question
is this, what is

00:11:06.958 --> 00:11:11.045 align:middle line:84%
the stuff the viewer's
consciousness is traveling

00:11:11.045 --> 00:11:13.882 align:middle line:84%
through that allows the
viewer to see countries

00:11:13.882 --> 00:11:16.342 align:middle line:84%
in secret locations on the
other side of the planet?

00:11:16.342 --> 00:11:18.553 align:middle line:84%
In a nutshell, the
question is this.

00:11:18.553 --> 00:11:21.306 align:middle line:84%
It all boils down
to what is in what

00:11:21.306 --> 00:11:23.933 align:middle line:84%
we call the empty
space of the universe.

00:11:23.933 --> 00:11:26.686 align:middle line:84%
What is in the space
of the nothing?

00:11:26.686 --> 00:11:28.229 align:middle line:84%
Well, to answer
this question, we've

00:11:28.229 --> 00:11:29.814 align:middle line:84%
opened the door to
one of the greatest

00:11:29.814 --> 00:11:32.275 align:middle line:84%
mysteries of our
existence, a mystery

00:11:32.275 --> 00:11:35.737 align:middle line:84%
that our ancestors describe
in the language of their time,

00:11:35.737 --> 00:11:38.114 align:middle line:84%
and that modern science
is just beginning

00:11:38.114 --> 00:11:40.867 align:middle line:90%
to understand in ours.

00:11:40.867 --> 00:11:44.329 align:middle line:84%
Almost universally, ancient
texts and Indigenous traditions

00:11:44.329 --> 00:11:48.165 align:middle line:84%
describe a field of energy
that connects all things.

00:11:48.165 --> 00:11:52.003 align:middle line:84%
I want to give you some examples
for how those descriptions have

00:11:52.003 --> 00:11:53.796 align:middle line:84%
been created in the
past so that you

00:11:53.796 --> 00:11:57.634 align:middle line:84%
can see the parallels to
what we now know exist today.

00:11:57.634 --> 00:12:01.429 align:middle line:84%
Chief Seattle, a 19th century
elder of the Suquamish people,

00:12:01.429 --> 00:12:03.056 align:middle line:84%
he described this
mystery, and I'm

00:12:03.056 --> 00:12:05.141 align:middle line:90%
going to read this specifically.

00:12:05.141 --> 00:12:07.936 align:middle line:84%
He said, "All things
are connected.

00:12:07.936 --> 00:12:11.731 align:middle line:84%
Man did not weave
the web of life.

00:12:11.731 --> 00:12:13.566 align:middle line:90%
He's merely a strand in it.

00:12:13.566 --> 00:12:17.820 align:middle line:84%
And whatever he does to the
web, he does to himself."

00:12:17.820 --> 00:12:20.615 align:middle line:84%
In the processes of
the ancient Hopi,

00:12:20.615 --> 00:12:24.452 align:middle line:84%
there are descriptions of
a web, or a net as well.

00:12:24.452 --> 00:12:26.704 align:middle line:10%
And this comes from
the Hopi prophecy

00:12:26.704 --> 00:12:30.875 align:middle line:10%
of what happened after the
first world of the Hopi

00:12:30.875 --> 00:12:32.627 align:middle line:10%
was threatened.

00:12:32.627 --> 00:12:35.713 align:middle line:10%
Spider Grandmother emerged
after the destruction

00:12:35.713 --> 00:12:37.006 align:middle line:10%
of the first world.

00:12:37.006 --> 00:12:39.300 align:middle line:10%
She emerged into
the Second World.

00:12:39.300 --> 00:12:41.511 align:middle line:10%
And the first thing
that she did was

00:12:41.511 --> 00:12:44.806 align:middle line:10%
she wove the web of
creation, upon which

00:12:44.806 --> 00:12:47.016 align:middle line:10%
her children and
her grandchildren

00:12:47.016 --> 00:12:50.645 align:middle line:10%
and all things in the
universe could exist.

00:12:50.645 --> 00:12:53.856 align:middle line:84%
Now I want to share with you
the exact words from the Hopi

00:12:53.856 --> 00:12:57.610 align:middle line:84%
prophecy describing
how this happened.

00:12:57.610 --> 00:13:00.738 align:middle line:10%
This is a quote, "When
the universe was still

00:13:00.738 --> 00:13:05.034 align:middle line:10%
so dark that not even shadows
could be seen in the night,

00:13:05.034 --> 00:13:09.372 align:middle line:10%
Spider Grandmother began to
sing her weaving song while she

00:13:09.372 --> 00:13:11.541 align:middle line:10%
danced across the sky.

00:13:11.541 --> 00:13:14.794 align:middle line:10%
As she spun her
thread, the Sky World

00:13:14.794 --> 00:13:18.673 align:middle line:10%
filled with light and
life as the stars, suns,

00:13:18.673 --> 00:13:22.176 align:middle line:10%
and the planets prepared to
give birth to their children."

00:13:22.176 --> 00:13:23.845 align:middle line:84%
Well, you can see
from this description,

00:13:23.845 --> 00:13:25.805 align:middle line:90%
it certainly is not scientific.

00:13:25.805 --> 00:13:29.058 align:middle line:10%
But it is telling us that
this universal essence,

00:13:29.058 --> 00:13:32.520 align:middle line:10%
this substance, what
the Hopi saw as a "web"

00:13:32.520 --> 00:13:36.149 align:middle line:10%
was what began the
beginning of the universe

00:13:36.149 --> 00:13:38.192 align:middle line:10%
as we know it today.

00:13:38.192 --> 00:13:40.111 align:middle line:90%
Well, the Hopi aren't alone.

00:13:40.111 --> 00:13:42.864 align:middle line:84%
In a similar way, the
ancient Buddhist traditions

00:13:42.864 --> 00:13:48.494 align:middle line:84%
describe how the great god Indra
created the web of creation.

00:13:48.494 --> 00:13:51.998 align:middle line:84%
"Far away in the heavenly
abode of the great god Indra,"

00:13:51.998 --> 00:13:54.625 align:middle line:84%
the texts say, "there
is a wonderful net

00:13:54.625 --> 00:13:58.171 align:middle line:84%
that stretches out
infinitely in all directions.

00:13:58.171 --> 00:14:01.591 align:middle line:84%
And at the intersection
of each point on the net

00:14:01.591 --> 00:14:04.302 align:middle line:90%
is a glittering jewel of light.

00:14:04.302 --> 00:14:07.930 align:middle line:84%
And that light is a
universe unto itself."

00:14:07.930 --> 00:14:10.224 align:middle line:84%
Well, the scientific
community is

00:14:10.224 --> 00:14:12.518 align:middle line:84%
beginning to describe
a structure that

00:14:12.518 --> 00:14:16.981 align:middle line:84%
sounds very similar to the
Hopi web and to India's net.

00:14:16.981 --> 00:14:20.359 align:middle line:84%
It's a structure that
underlies our everyday reality.

00:14:20.359 --> 00:14:23.571 align:middle line:10%
And even Einstein sensed that
this structure was there,

00:14:23.571 --> 00:14:26.657 align:middle line:10%
although as a scientist,
interestingly he shared it

00:14:26.657 --> 00:14:29.368 align:middle line:10%
from a very poetic description.

00:14:29.368 --> 00:14:31.204 align:middle line:10%
What Einstein said
to us, he said,

00:14:31.204 --> 00:14:35.040 align:middle line:10%
"Nature shows us only
the tail of the lion."

00:14:35.040 --> 00:14:38.377 align:middle line:10%
He says, "I do not doubt that
the lion belongs to the tail,

00:14:38.377 --> 00:14:41.756 align:middle line:10%
even though he cannot at once
reveal himself because of his

00:14:41.756 --> 00:14:43.716 align:middle line:10%
enormous size."

00:14:43.716 --> 00:14:46.511 align:middle line:10%
So what Einstein was saying,
from his perspective,

00:14:46.511 --> 00:14:48.304 align:middle line:10%
is there's something out there.

00:14:48.304 --> 00:14:52.725 align:middle line:84%
It's so big, but we cannot see
it from our vantage point where

00:14:52.725 --> 00:14:55.103 align:middle line:90%
we are in space and time.

00:14:55.103 --> 00:14:58.147 align:middle line:84%
And this underlying thinking
played a powerful role

00:14:58.147 --> 00:15:00.900 align:middle line:84%
as he developed his theories
of relativity and some

00:15:00.900 --> 00:15:04.195 align:middle line:84%
of the other theories
and mathematics concepts

00:15:04.195 --> 00:15:06.906 align:middle line:90%
that led to those theories.

00:15:06.906 --> 00:15:10.201 align:middle line:84%
So there's a common
theme that weaves its way

00:15:10.201 --> 00:15:12.245 align:middle line:84%
through each of
these descriptions,

00:15:12.245 --> 00:15:14.288 align:middle line:84%
through the web of
Spider Grandmother,

00:15:14.288 --> 00:15:15.998 align:middle line:84%
through the net
of the god Indra,

00:15:15.998 --> 00:15:19.502 align:middle line:84%
and through Einstein's
perspective, this idea

00:15:19.502 --> 00:15:23.589 align:middle line:84%
that there is something out
there that connects all things.

00:15:23.589 --> 00:15:25.383 align:middle line:84%
Well, in the beginning
of this program,

00:15:25.383 --> 00:15:29.470 align:middle line:84%
I shared Max Planck's statement,
his perspective of this essence

00:15:29.470 --> 00:15:30.263 align:middle line:90%
as well.

00:15:30.263 --> 00:15:32.723 align:middle line:84%
And Planck's statement
of this matrix

00:15:32.723 --> 00:15:34.851 align:middle line:84%
that underlies our
physical reality

00:15:34.851 --> 00:15:38.688 align:middle line:84%
is a perfect example of what
this thinking is all about.

00:15:38.688 --> 00:15:42.525 align:middle line:84%
So the question is,
what is this made of?

00:15:42.525 --> 00:15:45.361 align:middle line:84%
What is the web or the
net or the matrix made of?

00:15:45.361 --> 00:15:48.489 align:middle line:84%
And what are the rules that
govern this fundamental field

00:15:48.489 --> 00:15:49.282 align:middle line:90%
of energy?

00:15:49.282 --> 00:15:51.993 align:middle line:84%
And what does it mean
to us in our lives?

00:15:51.993 --> 00:15:55.705 align:middle line:84%
Well, in Season 1 of "Missing
Links," the Fifth Episode,

00:15:55.705 --> 00:15:58.332 align:middle line:84%
I described an experiment
performed in Switzerland

00:15:58.332 --> 00:16:01.752 align:middle line:84%
at the University
of Geneva in 1997.

00:16:01.752 --> 00:16:03.921 align:middle line:84%
I want to summarize the
experiment for you now.

00:16:03.921 --> 00:16:05.590 align:middle line:84%
And I'm going to do
it from a little bit

00:16:05.590 --> 00:16:07.466 align:middle line:84%
different perspective,
with a little bit

00:16:07.466 --> 00:16:11.470 align:middle line:84%
different emphasis from what
I did in that first season.

00:16:11.470 --> 00:16:13.264 align:middle line:84%
The experiment itself,
it was no secret.

00:16:13.264 --> 00:16:16.767 align:middle line:10%
It was reported over 3,400
journalists, educators,

00:16:16.767 --> 00:16:19.478 align:middle line:10%
scientists, and
engineers, in more than 40

00:16:19.478 --> 00:16:21.147 align:middle line:10%
different countries.

00:16:21.147 --> 00:16:24.483 align:middle line:10%
And the experiment
simply goes like this.

00:16:24.483 --> 00:16:28.362 align:middle line:84%
Scientists took a photon,
a particle of light.

00:16:28.362 --> 00:16:31.199 align:middle line:84%
This is the stuff the
atoms are made of.

00:16:31.199 --> 00:16:33.034 align:middle line:90%
They took a single photon.

00:16:33.034 --> 00:16:35.328 align:middle line:84%
They wanted to create
two identical photons.

00:16:35.328 --> 00:16:39.248 align:middle line:84%
So they took the one and broke
it into two separate photons

00:16:39.248 --> 00:16:42.877 align:middle line:84%
so that each one would
have identical properties.

00:16:42.877 --> 00:16:47.006 align:middle line:84%
And those two photons, they
isolated into a chamber.

00:16:47.006 --> 00:16:50.927 align:middle line:84%
And from this chamber, they
used fiber optic cables,

00:16:50.927 --> 00:16:52.678 align:middle line:90%
moving in opposite directions.

00:16:52.678 --> 00:16:57.600 align:middle line:84%
And one cable went seven miles
to a town seven miles away.

00:16:57.600 --> 00:17:00.061 align:middle line:84%
The other cable went seven
miles to another town

00:17:00.061 --> 00:17:05.316 align:middle line:84%
seven miles away from the place
where these photons began.

00:17:05.316 --> 00:17:08.861 align:middle line:84%
Each of the photons
was shot seven miles

00:17:08.861 --> 00:17:10.655 align:middle line:90%
in opposite directions.

00:17:10.655 --> 00:17:12.031 align:middle line:84%
So when they reached
their targets

00:17:12.031 --> 00:17:13.574 align:middle line:90%
they were 14 miles apart.

00:17:13.574 --> 00:17:15.409 align:middle line:84%
And this is where the
experiments actually

00:17:15.409 --> 00:17:18.621 align:middle line:84%
began, because what
the scientists found

00:17:18.621 --> 00:17:23.251 align:middle line:84%
was whatever they did to one
of the photons in one location,

00:17:23.251 --> 00:17:26.796 align:middle line:84%
in one moment in time,
the other photon acted

00:17:26.796 --> 00:17:30.716 align:middle line:84%
like it was having exactly
the same experience at exactly

00:17:30.716 --> 00:17:32.885 align:middle line:90%
the same moment in time.

00:17:32.885 --> 00:17:36.681 align:middle line:10%
They used atomic clocks to
tell them how long it took,

00:17:36.681 --> 00:17:40.184 align:middle line:10%
how much time did it take
for the information to move

00:17:40.184 --> 00:17:41.769 align:middle line:10%
from one photon to the other.

00:17:41.769 --> 00:17:44.855 align:middle line:84%
And this is where the problems
begin, because the atomic clock

00:17:44.855 --> 00:17:46.691 align:middle line:90%
said the time was zero.

00:17:46.691 --> 00:17:47.858 align:middle line:90%
There was no lag time.

00:17:47.858 --> 00:17:49.902 align:middle line:90%
It was instantaneous.

00:17:49.902 --> 00:17:52.196 align:middle line:10%
This breaks the rules
of Einstein's theory

00:17:52.196 --> 00:17:53.572 align:middle line:10%
of relativity.

00:17:53.572 --> 00:17:55.658 align:middle line:84%
Relativity says that
nothing can travel faster

00:17:55.658 --> 00:17:57.243 align:middle line:90%
than the speed of light.

00:17:57.243 --> 00:18:00.496 align:middle line:84%
For the two photons to have
exactly the same experience

00:18:00.496 --> 00:18:03.374 align:middle line:84%
at exactly the same
time with no lag time

00:18:03.374 --> 00:18:05.251 align:middle line:84%
means that somehow
the information

00:18:05.251 --> 00:18:09.672 align:middle line:84%
had to move from point A
to point B instantaneously,

00:18:09.672 --> 00:18:11.882 align:middle line:90%
faster than the speed of light.

00:18:11.882 --> 00:18:14.385 align:middle line:84%
This is where the
problems began.

00:18:14.385 --> 00:18:17.722 align:middle line:84%
So the behavior of the
photons is a problem

00:18:17.722 --> 00:18:19.890 align:middle line:90%
for conventional physics.

00:18:19.890 --> 00:18:24.687 align:middle line:84%
Those photons are defying the
laws of conventional physics.

00:18:24.687 --> 00:18:27.773 align:middle line:84%
However, they conform to
the laws of relativity.

00:18:27.773 --> 00:18:30.067 align:middle line:84%
And this is where the
experiment becomes

00:18:30.067 --> 00:18:31.986 align:middle line:84%
very relevant to
everything that we're

00:18:31.986 --> 00:18:36.449 align:middle line:84%
talking about when we talk
about this matrix of energy.

00:18:36.449 --> 00:18:40.870 align:middle line:84%
What the experiment tells us
is that particles that are once

00:18:40.870 --> 00:18:46.584 align:middle line:84%
joined physically remain
linked energetically

00:18:46.584 --> 00:18:50.254 align:middle line:84%
even though they are physically
separated from one another.

00:18:50.254 --> 00:18:53.466 align:middle line:84%
Two photons were
once a single photon.

00:18:53.466 --> 00:18:56.886 align:middle line:84%
Even though they were split
into two separate photons,

00:18:56.886 --> 00:18:59.722 align:middle line:84%
energetically, they
were connected.

00:18:59.722 --> 00:19:02.016 align:middle line:84%
The term is called
entanglement--

00:19:02.016 --> 00:19:03.684 align:middle line:90%
quantum entanglement.

00:19:03.684 --> 00:19:06.729 align:middle line:84%
And what it means is that
whatever is happening

00:19:06.729 --> 00:19:08.981 align:middle line:84%
to one of those
photons in one place,

00:19:08.981 --> 00:19:11.859 align:middle line:84%
whether it's 14 miles from the
other one on the other side

00:19:11.859 --> 00:19:13.944 align:middle line:84%
of the planet or in the
other side of the universe

00:19:13.944 --> 00:19:16.197 align:middle line:84%
is irrelevant,
they're entangled.

00:19:16.197 --> 00:19:21.369 align:middle line:84%
And they will always reflect
the exact same parameters in one

00:19:21.369 --> 00:19:23.579 align:middle line:90%
that are happening to the other.

00:19:23.579 --> 00:19:26.165 align:middle line:84%
Let me tell you why
this is so powerful, why

00:19:26.165 --> 00:19:28.209 align:middle line:90%
this is so important.

00:19:28.209 --> 00:19:32.463 align:middle line:84%
If we think about the
model of creation,

00:19:32.463 --> 00:19:34.882 align:middle line:84%
if we think about our
universe, scientists

00:19:34.882 --> 00:19:39.428 align:middle line:84%
tell us that the universe began
with a tremendous release,

00:19:39.428 --> 00:19:42.932 align:middle line:84%
a primal release of energy
that we call the Big Bang.

00:19:42.932 --> 00:19:45.142 align:middle line:84%
In the Big Bang,
energy was released,

00:19:45.142 --> 00:19:47.144 align:middle line:90%
and it began to expand.

00:19:47.144 --> 00:19:50.398 align:middle line:84%
And physical matter began
to expand and move away

00:19:50.398 --> 00:19:54.610 align:middle line:84%
from the point of the
release of the energy.

00:19:54.610 --> 00:19:58.239 align:middle line:84%
If we could reverse
the Big Bang,

00:19:58.239 --> 00:20:00.366 align:middle line:84%
if we could take
that physical matter

00:20:00.366 --> 00:20:04.161 align:middle line:84%
and bring it all back to the
point where it all began,

00:20:04.161 --> 00:20:07.540 align:middle line:84%
what scientists tell us
is, at that moment just

00:20:07.540 --> 00:20:10.751 align:middle line:84%
after the release of energy,
all the matter in the universe,

00:20:10.751 --> 00:20:13.546 align:middle line:84%
as big as the universe
appears, all that matter

00:20:13.546 --> 00:20:19.677 align:middle line:84%
would fit into the space about
the size of a single green pea,

00:20:19.677 --> 00:20:23.180 align:middle line:84%
that all the physical matter
from all of the bodies, all

00:20:23.180 --> 00:20:27.059 align:middle line:84%
of the planets, all the stars,
all of that physical matter

00:20:27.059 --> 00:20:29.520 align:middle line:84%
which is believed to
take up only about 4%

00:20:29.520 --> 00:20:30.938 align:middle line:84%
of the whole
universe-- scientists

00:20:30.938 --> 00:20:33.774 align:middle line:84%
tell us 96% of the
matter is missing.

00:20:33.774 --> 00:20:36.777 align:middle line:84%
96% of our universe,
they believe, is empty.

00:20:36.777 --> 00:20:41.824 align:middle line:10%
So that 4% would be compacted
into a single sphere

00:20:41.824 --> 00:20:45.870 align:middle line:10%
about the size of a green pea,
a really hot single sphere.

00:20:45.870 --> 00:20:48.456 align:middle line:84%
They tell us about 18
billion, million, million,

00:20:48.456 --> 00:20:49.874 align:middle line:90%
million degrees.

00:20:49.874 --> 00:20:51.959 align:middle line:84%
And when I talked to the
scientists about that,

00:20:51.959 --> 00:20:53.419 align:middle line:84%
I said, now how do
you really know that?

00:20:53.419 --> 00:20:54.628 align:middle line:90%
And they say, well, we don't.

00:20:54.628 --> 00:20:57.256 align:middle line:84%
[CHUCKLES] They say, but we
know that it was really hot.

00:20:57.256 --> 00:21:01.635 align:middle line:84%
So when all of that matter was
compressed into that single

00:21:01.635 --> 00:21:03.429 align:middle line:90%
green pea-- here's the key--

00:21:03.429 --> 00:21:05.055 align:middle line:90%
everything was connected.

00:21:05.055 --> 00:21:06.724 align:middle line:90%
Everything was connected.

00:21:06.724 --> 00:21:11.770 align:middle line:84%
And even though the force
of that primal release

00:21:11.770 --> 00:21:13.981 align:middle line:84%
has allowed the
universe to expand,

00:21:13.981 --> 00:21:16.942 align:middle line:84%
and it's expanding today,
and the physical matter

00:21:16.942 --> 00:21:19.612 align:middle line:84%
is no longer
physically connected,

00:21:19.612 --> 00:21:22.114 align:middle line:84%
the experiment that we
saw with the twin photons

00:21:22.114 --> 00:21:25.326 align:middle line:84%
